<h1 class="page-header text-center">Support Hero Scheduler</h1>

<div class="row login-wrapper">
  <div class="col-sm-offset-4 col-sm-4">

    <%= simple_form_for(resource, as: resource_name, url: session_path(resource_name)) do |f| %>
      <div class="field">
        <%= f.input :login, autofocus: true %>
      </div>

      <div class="field">
        <%= f.input :password, autocomplete: "off" %>
      </div>

      <div class="actions">
        <%= f.submit 'Log in', class: 'btn btn-primary stretch' %>
      </div>
    <% end %>

    <p class="text-center">Notes</p>
    <hr>
    <p>Test user credentials have been auto-inserted. You can also log in as another user, like 'sherry', 'jay', or 'zoe', all using password '123abc!!'.</p>

    <p>I had to make some compromises given my limited time. Checking holidays is done against 'United States' holidays as opposed to 'California' holidays. Also, my tests are minimal and cover the low hanging fruit cases.</p>
  </div>
</div>
